NodeJS.

    - NodeJS is the Server Side Scripting Language.

    - By using NodeJS We Can Create either http (or) tco servers.

    - As a Node Developer We Can Assign Port Numbers to the Servers.

    - Node Application itself Acting as a Server as well as Business Component.


Modules in NodeJS.

1.express

    - used to develop the Rest API in Node Applications.


2.mysql

    - it is used to communicate with the mysql database.


3.mongodb

    - it is used to communicate with the mongodb.


4.body-parser

    -- it is used to set the MIME Type.


5.jwt-simple

    -- it is used to maintain the Token Based Authentication System.


6. fs
    -- used to interact with the flat files.



